body:
### Welcome to MagStriper.
MagStriper is an application to read and write (encode) magnetic stripe cards.

The software features read, write, compare, duplicate, and erase support for MSR206-compatible readers and writers (including MSRW MSR606, MSR505C, MSR106, MSR406, MSR210, MSR210U, and others).

####[Download MagStriper for Mac OS X](https://s3.amazonaws.com/GitHub/MagStriper.zip)



[![Screen Shot](https://s3.amazonaws.com/GitHub/MagStriperScreenShot.png)](https://s3.amazonaws.com/GitHub/MagStriperScreenShot.png)

***

### System Requirements
* Mac OS X 10.8 (Mountain Lion) or higher
* Serial or USB interface on the device
* Drivers are required to expose the serial interface. USB drivers for some devices are available directly from [Prolific](http://www.prolific.com.tw/US/supportDownload.aspx?FileType=56&FileID=133&pcid=85&Page=0)

### Support or Contact

* [Installation & Setup](https://github.com/kevinbrewster/MagStriper/wiki/Installation-and-Setup)
* [How to Use](https://github.com/kevinbrewster/MagStriper/wiki/How-to-Use)

Having trouble with MagStriper? Check out the documentation at https://github.com/kevinbrewster/MagStriper/wiki/_pages or report an issue [here](https://github.com/kevinbrewster/MagStriper/issues)  and weâ€™ll help you sort it out.


### Authors and Contributors
MagStriper is written and maintained by @KevinBrewster. Thanks to @lid for [MagTool](https://github.com/lid/MagTool) @davedelong for [CHCSVParser](https://github.com/davedelong/CHCSVParser) and @armadsen for [ORSerialPort](https://github.com/armadsen/ORSSerialPort).
